[[File:Watatsu jinja 2nd Gate.JPG|thumb|right|Torii at Watatsu-jinja]]
{{nihongo|'''Watatsu-jinja'''|度津神社||}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Sado, Niigata]] off the west coast of the island of [[Honshu]] in the [[Sea of Japan]].<ref>VisitSado.com, [http://www.visitsado.com/en/01outline/08pt_09/06.shtml  Watatsu Shrine]; retrieved 2012-11-6.</ref> 

==History==
The enshrined ''[[kami]]'' is  {{nihongo|Isonotakeru no mikoto|五十猛命||}}, who is said to have taught people shipbuilding and how to use ships.<ref>Kotodamaya.com, [http://www.kotodamaya.com/watatsu-jinja/  "Watatsu Jinja"]; retrieved 2012-11-6.</ref>

Watatsu was the chief Shinto shrine (''[[ichinomiya]]'') of the old [[Sado Province]] on [[Sado Island]].  It serves today as one of the ''ichinomiya'' of [[Niigata Prefecture]].  
<ref>[http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/images/uploads/EOS070712Ab.pdf "Nationwide List of ''Ichinomiya''," p. 2]; retrieved 2012-3-13.</ref>

In the [[modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines]], Watatsu was listed among the 3rd class of nationally significant shrines or {{nihongo|''Kokuhei Shōsha''|国幣小社}}.

==Related pages==
* [[List of Shinto shrines in Japan]]
* [[Modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines]]

